Probability	#472.	 count upon &c. (believe). Adj. probable, likely, hopeful, to be expected, in a fair way. plausible, specious, ostensible, colorable, ben trovato [It], well-founded, reasonable, credible, easy of belief, presumable, presumptive, apparent. Adv. probably &c. adj.
Intuition. & Sophistry	#477.	 specious, hollow, plausible, ad captandum [Lat.], evasive
Beauty	#845.	 glossy, sleek. rich, superb, magnificent, grand, fine, sublime, showy, specious. artistic, artistical
Flattery	#933.	 soapy, oily, unctuous, blandiloquent, specious
Vindication	#937.	 specious, plausible, justifiable. Phr. honi sot qui mal y pense
